The paper proposes a methodology for extracting and aggregating per-move evaluations from sets of Go game records, which can be utilized to predict different relevant target variables such as player strength and playing style. This involves the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), game theory (cs.GT), or computational linguistics (cs.CL) as natural language processing techniques could potentially be used in the analysis of game records.
